---
/**
 * /methodology — discipline overview.
 *
 * Per deck §06: "What decision cartography is, how PIN practices it."
 * Per deck §03: methodology architecture is layered
 *   Worldview → Operating system (CROWD POWERED) → Firm → Discipline → Validation → Outputs
 *
 * This page anchors the three sub-pages:
 *   /methodology/framework   — CROWD POWERED 12-step
 *   /methodology/curriculum  — PINU 8-phase
 *   /methodology/validation  — VERIDEX
 */
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '@/components/PageHero.astro';
import SectionMarker from '@/components/SectionMarker.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Methodology — Decision Cartography · Power In Numbers"
  description="Decision cartography is the discipline of mapping rigorous, validated, defensible paths to high-stakes outcomes under uncertainty. The methodology is composed of a 12-step framework (CROWD POWERED), an 8-phase development curriculum, and a validation layer (VERIDEX)."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="The discipline"
    headline="Decision cartography."
    lede="The discipline of mapping rigorous, validated, defensible paths to <em>high-stakes outcomes</em> under uncertainty."
    meta="A methodology · A 12-step framework · An 8-phase curriculum · A validation layer"
  />

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      §01 — What it is, said plainly
      ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 01" tag="The discipline, defined" />

      <div class="prose">
        <p data-reveal>
          The major strategy consultancies sell engagements. Power In Numbers
          practices a <em>discipline</em>. The difference is consequential. An
          engagement is sized to a budget and produces a deck. A discipline is
          sized to a question and produces a map &mdash; one that can be opened
          again, audited, falsified, and defended in a room of skeptics.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal>
          We call the discipline <em>decision cartography</em>. The metaphor does
          three things at once. It names the discipline. It describes the
          deliverable: a map &mdash; with coordinates, a legend, and a
          counterfactual landscape. And it tells the reader what the work looks
          like on the screen: charts, frameworks, monochrome line work, audit
          trails. Literally cartography.
        </p>
        <p data-reveal>
          The methodology underneath the discipline is composed of three
          working systems. A 12-step framework (CROWD POWERED) governs <em>how
          ventures are structured</em> &mdash; participatory and reinvesting
          rather than extractive, with mission-focused ventures returning
          ninety percent of revenue back into the business itself. An 8-phase
          curriculum (PINU) governs how practitioners are formed. A validation
          layer (VERIDEX) governs which maps can leave the firm.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="pull" data-reveal>
        <p class="pull__quote">
          The deliverable is a map: actionable, feasible, data-driven,
          defensible. VERIDEX validates the map.
        </p>
        <p class="pull__attr">From the brand brief, §03</p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      §02 — The four properties of a defensible map
      ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section section--paper-deep">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 02" tag="What makes a map defensible" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        Four properties &mdash; each testable, each falsifiable.
      </h2>

      <div class="props" data-reveal>
        <article class="prop">
          <span class="prop__num">01</span>
          <h3 class="prop__name">Actionable</h3>
          <p class="prop__body">
            Every option on the map can be implemented by an identifiable
            actor with an identifiable budget and an identifiable timeline. A
            map that recommends "alignment" without naming who funds it is
            not a map. It's a wish.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="prop">
          <span class="prop__num">02</span>
          <h3 class="prop__name">Feasible</h3>
          <p class="prop__body">
            Each path has been tested against fiscal, political, regulatory,
            and operational constraints. A feasibility test that returns
            "yes" without enumerating the constraints it overcame is not a
            test. It's a hope.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="prop">
          <span class="prop__num">03</span>
          <h3 class="prop__name">Data-driven</h3>
          <p class="prop__body">
            Every figure on the map has a citation. Every model run has a
            date and a parameter set. Every Monte Carlo has a seed. The map
            survives an external auditor reading it cold.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="prop">
          <span class="prop__num">04</span>
          <h3 class="prop__name">Defensible</h3>
          <p class="prop__body">
            The map has been pressure-tested against its own counterfactual.
            For every recommended path, a peer path has been constructed,
            scored, and rejected on stated grounds. The reader sees what was
            not chosen and why.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      §03 — The three systems
      ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 03" tag="The three working systems" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        How the methodology is operated.
      </h2>
      <p class="s-lede" data-reveal>
        Each system is necessary and none is sufficient. The framework
        constructs the map. The curriculum forms the cartographer. The
        validation layer governs what may be published.
      </p>

      <div class="systems" data-reveal>
        <article class="system">
          <header class="system__head">
            <span class="system__num">System 01</span>
            <h3 class="system__name">CROWD POWERED <span class="system__qual">— the framework</span></h3>
          </header>
          <p class="system__claim">
            A 12-step framework &mdash; the letters of the name are the steps,
            in order &mdash; for structuring participatory ventures in any
            industry. Industry-agnostic. Originally taught 2003.
          </p>
          <p class="system__detail">
            A sustainable, virtuous-cycle generalization of crowdfunding into a
            full operating discipline. Four movements: Resource Optimization,
            Community Building, Market Expansion, Sustainable Scale. For
            mission-focused ventures, the closing rule is structural: ninety
            percent of revenue is reinvested back into the business itself.
          </p>
          <a href="/methodology/framework" class="readmore">Read the framework &rarr;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="system">
          <header class="system__head">
            <span class="system__num">System 02</span>
            <h3 class="system__name">The Curriculum <span class="system__qual">— the formation</span></h3>
          </header>
          <p class="system__claim">
            An 8-phase development curriculum (PINU) for forming practitioners
            of decision cartography &mdash; firm-internal staff, client teams
            embedded for a project, and select cohorts.
          </p>
          <p class="system__detail">
            The curriculum exists because the framework is not a checklist. It
            is a discipline, and disciplines are taught by apprenticeship. PINU
            structures the apprenticeship: from the development question through
            counterfactual reasoning, scenario construction, validation,
            briefing.
          </p>
          <a href="/methodology/curriculum" class="readmore">Read the curriculum &rarr;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="system">
          <header class="system__head">
            <span class="system__num">System 03</span>
            <h3 class="system__name">VERIDEX <span class="system__qual">— the validation layer</span></h3>
          </header>
          <p class="system__claim">
            The QA layer. A gate-by-gate audit that every map must pass before
            the firm releases it. The only named public system at v1.
          </p>
          <p class="system__detail">
            VERIDEX is a fixed set of validation gates &mdash; coverage of
            counterfactual, citation integrity, parameter declaration, scenario
            envelope, briefing legibility, and others. A map either passes
            22/22 or it does not leave the firm. The gates are public; the
            specific scoring is held to deliverable.
          </p>
          <a href="/methodology/validation" class="readmore">Read the validation layer &rarr;</a>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      §04 — How an engagement runs
      ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section section--paper-deep">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 04" tag="How an engagement runs" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        From the development question to the briefing.
      </h2>

      <ol class="flow" data-reveal>
        <li class="flow__step">
          <span class="flow__num">01</span>
          <h3 class="flow__name">The development question</h3>
          <p>
            Every engagement begins with a single, falsifiable question. Not a
            theme, not a goal, not an "area of focus." A question that can be
            answered yes, no, or with a quantified maybe. The question is the
            seed of the map.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="flow__step">
          <span class="flow__num">02</span>
          <h3 class="flow__name">The counterfactual pause</h3>
          <p>
            Before any options are scored, the team builds the counterfactual
            landscape: the world in which the firm does nothing, and the world
            in which a peer firm acts instead. Most strategy work skips this
            step. We do not.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="flow__step">
          <span class="flow__num">03</span>
          <h3 class="flow__name">The cartography</h3>
          <p>
            The framework is run. Options are constructed, scored, and embedded
            in a scenario envelope. Where stochastic elements warrant it, Monte
            Carlo simulation is run with declared parameters and seed.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="flow__step">
          <span class="flow__num">04</span>
          <h3 class="flow__name">VERIDEX validation</h3>
          <p>
            The map is submitted to the validation gates. Failures are
            remediated; the map is re-run; the audit log is preserved. A map
            that does not pass 22/22 does not leave the firm.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="flow__step">
          <span class="flow__num">05</span>
          <h3 class="flow__name">The decision-maker briefing</h3>
          <p>
            The deliverable is an interactive, browser-native map &mdash; not
            a PDF, not a PowerPoint &mdash; opened with the principal in the
            room. The reader can audit any cell, follow any citation, and run
            any scenario themselves.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      §05 — The deliverable form
      ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 05" tag="The deliverable form" />

      <h2 class="s-title" data-reveal>
        Why the deliverable is interactive, not a deck.
      </h2>

      <div class="compare" data-reveal>
        <div class="compare__col compare__col--isnt">
          <p class="compare__label">What it isn't</p>
          <ul class="anti-list">
            <li>A 60-slide PDF.</li>
            <li>A PowerPoint with three tiers of recommendations.</li>
            <li>A consultancy "playbook" that reads as a sales asset.</li>
            <li>A dashboard mistaken for a decision.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="compare__col compare__col--is">
          <p class="compare__label">What it is</p>
          <ul class="anti-list anti-list--is">
            <li>An interactive, browser-native map.</li>
            <li>Audit-traced &mdash; every figure has a citation.</li>
            <li>Counterfactual-aware &mdash; the rejected paths are visible.</li>
            <li>VERIDEX-validated &mdash; the audit log travels with the map.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="compare__note" data-reveal>
        The Ghana fiscal framework, the US market entry, and each firm-built
        venture is delivered in this form. <a href="/case-studies/ghana-market-entry/">See the Ghana case</a>
        for an embedded replica of an actual deliverable.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  {/* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
      §06 — Three sub-pages
      ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
  <section class="section section--ink">
    <div class="frame">
      <SectionMarker num="§ 06" tag="Read further" inverse />

      <h2 class="s-title s-title--inverse" data-reveal>
        Three pages, each going deeper.
      </h2>

      <div class="next-grid" data-reveal>
        <a href="/methodology/framework" class="next-card">
          <span class="next-card__num">01</span>
          <span class="next-card__name">CROWD POWERED</span>
          <span class="next-card__qual">The 12-step framework</span>
          <span class="next-card__cta">Read &rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology/curriculum" class="next-card">
          <span class="next-card__num">02</span>
          <span class="next-card__name">The Curriculum</span>
          <span class="next-card__qual">The 8-phase formation</span>
          <span class="next-card__cta">Read &rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology/validation" class="next-card">
          <span class="next-card__num">03</span>
          <span class="next-card__name">VERIDEX</span>
          <span class="next-card__qual">The validation layer</span>
          <span class="next-card__cta">Read &rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .section {
    padding: 96px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .section { padding: 64px 0; } }
  .section--paper-deep { background: var(--paper-deep); }
  .section--ink { background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper); border-bottom: none; }

  .s-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 38px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .s-title { font-size: 28px; } }
  .s-title--inverse { color: var(--paper); }
  .s-lede {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 48px;
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  /* ----- Prose with pull quote ----- */
  .prose {
    max-width: 680px;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 24px; }
  .prose em { font-style: italic; color: var(--ink); }

  .pull {
    margin: 64px auto;
    max-width: 760px;
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .pull__quote {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 30px;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .pull__quote { font-size: 22px; } }
  .pull__attr {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--subtext);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ----- Properties grid (2x2) ----- */
  .props {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper);
    margin-top: 32px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .props { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .prop {
    padding: 32px 28px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .prop:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
  .prop:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: none; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .prop { border-right: none; }
    .prop:not(:last-child) { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink); }
    .prop:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  }
  .prop__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    color: var(--oxblood);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .prop__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .prop__body {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ----- Three systems ----- */
  .systems {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 980px) { .systems { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 16px; } }
  .system {
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .system__head {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
    padding: 18px 22px 16px;
  }
  .system__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    opacity: 0.6;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .system__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .system__qual {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.65);
    font-size: 18px;
  }
  .system__claim {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 22px 22px 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .system__detail {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 22px 22px;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .system .readmore { margin: 0 22px 22px; }

  /* ----- Engagement flow (numbered ol) ----- */
  .flow {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    counter-reset: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .flow__step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 240px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    padding: 28px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .flow__step:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink); }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .flow__step { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 8px; }
  }
  .flow__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--oxblood);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .flow__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 22px;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .flow__step p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ----- Compare (is / isn't) ----- */
  .compare {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .compare { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .compare__col {
    padding: 32px 28px;
  }
  .compare__col--isnt { background: var(--paper-deep); border-right: 1px solid var(--ink); }
  .compare__col--is { background: var(--paper); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .compare__col--isnt { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink); }
  }
  .compare__label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--oxblood);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .anti-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .anti-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--subtext);
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: var(--rule);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .anti-list--is li {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .compare__note {
    margin: 32px 0 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--subtext);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .compare__note a { color: var(--oxblood); }

  /* ----- Next grid (inverse, sub-page links) ----- */
  .next-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.25);
    margin-top: 32px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 860px) { .next-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .next-card {
    padding: 32px 28px;
    border-right: 1px solid rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.25);
    color: var(--paper);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    transition: background 0.18s ease;
  }
  .next-card:hover { background: rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.04); }
  .next-card:last-child { border-right: none; }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .next-card {
      border-right: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.25);
    }
    .next-card:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  }
  .next-card__num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: #D67878;
  }
  .next-card__name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 26px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .next-card__qual {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 16px;
    color: rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.7);
  }
  .next-card__cta {
    margin-top: auto;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(245, 241, 232, 0.4);
    padding-bottom: 4px;
    align-self: flex-start;
    transition: color 0.18s ease, border-color 0.18s ease;
  }
  .next-card:hover .next-card__cta { color: #F5E1A8; border-color: #F5E1A8; }
</style>
